name: Storj
description: Storj is a decentralized cloud storage platform that allows anyone to rent their idle hard drive space and to earn a revenue by doing so. End users can use Storj to store their files at competitive prices and within a p2p network that is secure from server downtime, censorship and hacks. Payments within the Storj network and conducted with the STORJ token, an ERC20 Ethereum-based token.

name: iExec RLC
description: RLC is an Ethereum-based token used in the iEx.ec, a blockchain-based distributed cloud computing platform. ???Developers can rent computing power, servers and data centers and make their unused resources available through a unique marketplace on the Ethereum blockchain. The RLC token allows users to rent servers, data and applications to execute their distributed applications.

name: SingularDTV
description: SingularDTV (S-DTV) is a decentralized and tokenized content creating and distributing platform that will create, acquire and distribute film and television content in an innovative way, generating revenue for its token holders in a completely transparent and decentralized manner.

name: Binance Coin
description: The Binance Coin is an Ethereum-based token that allows users to receive a discount for any fees on the Binance platform, a pure cryptocurrency exchange that plans to create a decentralized exchange for blockchain assets. BNB also gives users access to special features and will be used to power the upcoming decentralized exchange.

name: Bankcoin
description: Bitcoin is the first true digital peer to peer currency system that ushered in the era of cryptocurrency and related technologies. Bitcoin was announced by Satoshi Nakamoto in November 2008 and the first block was mined in January 2009. It???s code has been forked and used directly or indirectly for most of the other cryptocurrencies. Even when the code is not directly forked, Bitcoin has formed the basis of almost every other cryptocurrency in existence. Bitcoin is described in the original whitepaper as ???A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System??.

name: Prototanium
description: Primecoin is a proof of work cryptocurrency with a unique proof of work algorithm that finds chains of prime numbers. The purpose behind the creation of primecoin was to provide a proof of work system that can also produce useful output instead of simply throwing away the work done, as in the more popular SHA-256 of Scrypt hashing. Primecoin accepts three types of prime number chains ??"Cunningham Chainof the first kind, Cunningham Chain of the second kind and Bi-twin chain. Some of the largest Cunningham chains have been found by the Primecoin network.

name: Aragon
description: Aragon is an Ethereum based digital asset that powers the Aragon Network, a digital jurisdiction using smart contract architecture that intends to make decentralized organizations more efficient than traditional businesses. Aragon is intended to disintermediate businesses by using blockchain based applications and enabling borderless creation of value It is based on the idea of organizations aggregating multiple application components and a pillar called the Kernel. The applications and Kernel are governed via Aragon and interact via Aragon powered applications. The Aragon Network introduces seamless upgrades to businesses and uses a decentralized court system to solve human disputes. Aragon also manages the Aragon Institution MT???, an Estonian-based non-profit. Aragon helps to power the district0x Network.

name: GameCredits
description: GameCredits is an open source P2P cryptocurrency designed for in-game payments and pay-outs to developers and gamers that seeks to become a universal currency for gaming. This means they intend to design a frictionless payment gateway and blockchain-base in-game monetization platform. GameCredits is a technical clone of Litecoin before Segwit and was launched in 2016. GameCredits partnered with the giant gaming development and marketing company, Datcroft Games LTD. It protects assets with the GWallet.

name: Tierion
description: Tierion is a platform for data verification. Tierion works by creating a proof that links data to a transaction on a blockchain. This is called anchoring. Anyone with this proof can verify the data???s integrity and timestamp without relying on a trusted authority.

name: GXShares
description: The Gx Coin project is a cryptocurrency VC fund created by Genevieve that buys into local economies around the world in the form of business financing. The GXC is an Ethereum-based token and represents a stake in the fund.

name: Bitstar
description: Bitshares is a financial smart asset platform that has the ability to create ???Smart Assets??? that are backed by the native currency of Bitshares. The main innovation behind Bitshares has been the development of market-pegged assets that allow, within certain parameters, for an asset issued on the Bitshares blockchain to track the real-world value of that asset, be it US Dollars or ounces of gold.Bitshares was created by Daniel Larimer (aka Bytemaster) through a company Invictus Innovations, which was subsequently dissolved. Bitshares was the first cryptocurrency to introduce a Delegated Proof of Stake as the consensus mechanism, which allowed for block creation time to be 10 seconds.

Even when the code is not directly forked, Bitcoin has formed the basis of almost every other cryptocurrency in existence. Bitcoin is described in the original whitepaper as ???A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System??.

name: Aidos Kuneen
description: Aidos Kuneen is an open source privacy cryptocurrency focusing on security and preventing traceability. Aidos has zero fees, enabling micro transactions and IoT level scalability. Aidos transactions are based on directed mesh with I2P as the network layer and AKshuffle anonymizes users. IMesh is an innovation of DLT based on a directed acycling graph. Each transaction verifies two other transactions. Aidos enables a network wide active participant consensus mechanism allowing for self-regulating P2P modeling. Aidos involves no mining, is blockless, and has increasing block times to scale.

name: CloakCoin
description: CloakCoin is an open source, end-to-end encrypted cryptocurrency intended for private and untraceable digital cash transfers. This is meant to allow nodes to work around traffic on the blockchain. It uses symmetric RSA encryption backed by an ECDH key exchange. 6% annual interest is rewarded for staking the coins within the owner???s wallet. Complete transparency as the software is continually reviewed for bugs, tracking, and malware. CloakCoins can be sent using the Enigma system and is meant to become a privacy operating system. Uses Proof of Stake consensus. Users are able to share in the network???s 1.8% transaction fee to stake their support for the network. Intended to have a limited circulated supply.

name: Peercoin
description: Peercoin is a hybrid proof-of-stake / proof-of-work protocol based on Bitcoin. It has been designed with the goal of reaching long-term energy efficiency by incentivizing a minting of new coins through staking instead of mining after the initial distribution process. Peercoin retargets difficulty each block. It technically has a hard limit of 2 billion coins, but this is unlikely to be reached. Peercoin has an effective inflation rate of 1% per year.

name: Litecoin
description: Litecoin presently holds the number two rank in cryptocurrency market capitalization. Released on October 13th, 2011, Litecoin is an early fork of bitcoin that was designed by its creator, Charlie Lee to be ???silver to bitcoin???s gold.??? Litecoin???s block confirmation times are four times faster and total possible supply is quadruple that of bitcoin. Charlie Lee is currently employed as a developer at CoinBase and his brother, Bobby Lee, is the CEO and founder of the BTC China bitcoin exchange.

name: MCAP
description: MCAP is a tokenized investment fund by the BitcoinGroth Fund project. It focuses on mining and ICO investments. The MCAP coin is an Ethereum-based token and represents a share in the holdings of the MCAP fund.

name: Metal
description: Metalcoin is a minable cryptocurrency, backed by tangible assets. Miners will be able to mine MetalCoins with their computers and trade them in for actual gold, silver and copper coins (minted by MetalCoin), if they choose to sell. MetalCoin will also hold a derivative value based on future franchise ???performance. Word of warning as their website and twitter feeds are not working as of april 2015.

name: Cofound.it
description: Cofound.it is a digital asset for stake within the decentralized crowdfunding platform under the same name for blockchain enabled solutions. The utility of the cryptocurrency is a stake into the marketplace for new startups, to fund aspiring teams and help with early startup expenses. Cofound.it is meant to have internal ICOs and create an alternative to venture capitalists.

name: Iconomi
description: Iconomi is an European based exchange that allows users to easily acquire Ether with EUR. Iconomi has recently expanded into a crowdfunded project, the Iconomi Open Fund Management platform. In the Iconomi OFM, users can choose between two investment types with different risk and profit levels, Coin Traded Funds (CTFs) and Coin Managed Funds (CMFs).  Iconomi (ICN) tokens allow users to vote regarding the platform's development and they pay out dividends from the profits generated by the Iconomi OFM platform.

name: SALT
description: SALT is a membership based lending and borrowing network that allows users to leverage their blockchain assets to secure cash loans. The SALT Secured Automated Lending Technology is a protocol and asset agnostic architecture designed to adapt to the constantly growing class of blockchain assets.  The SALT Platform is automated and cryptographically secure. SALT is a lending platform specifically designed for blockchain assets; operating as a second layer protocol which sits atop any public or permissioned blockchain, allowing the underlying asset to be used as collateral for access to credit.

name: Veritaseum
description: Veritaseum is a smart contract-based wallet interface that allows anyone to create, enter and manage smart contracts without the need for any kind of intermediaries, middleman or centralized authority. Veritaseum will allow users to interact with real-world products based completely on blockchain technology and smart contracts, including P2P value trading, P2P letters of credit and DAOs. VERI tokens will allow users to interact with the Veritaseum wallet interface.

name: Melon
description: The Melon protocol is a blockchain protocol for digital asset management on the Ethereum platform. It enables participants to set up, manage and invest in digital asset management strategies in an open, competitive and decentralised manner. The usage token is called Melon token MLN and is a core component of the Melon project. It is designed to enjoy a ???usage right??? to the Melon protocol. To use the Melon protocol one has to use MLN token. This ???usage fee??? will most likely be imposed on trading.

name: Gulden
description: Gulden is a Netherlands based Dutch cryptocurrency that allows users to send and wire money transactions to any IBAN account. Can be exchanged through the Gulden iOS and Android mobile payment system apps. Gulden is able to spend anywhere where Bitcoin is accepted due to seamless transfers. Nocks is a Gulden blockchain-based money transfer system. Nocks is instantly able to convert Bitcoin and Euro to Gulden. The cryptocurrency uses an algorithm called DELTA that smoothens block times and makes mining fairer called PoW2.

name: OmiseGO
description: OmiseGO is building a decentralized exchange, liquidity provider mechanism, clearinghouse messaging network, and asset-backed blockchain gateway. OmiseGO is not owned by any single one party. Instead, it is an open distributed network of validators which enforce behavior of all participants. It uses the mechanism of a protocol token to create a proof-of-stake blockchain to enable enforcement of market activity amongst participants. Owning OMG tokens buys the right to validate this blockchain, within its consensus rules. Transaction fees on the network including payment, interchange, trading, and clearinghouse use, are given to non-faulty validators who enforce bonded contract states. The token will have value derived from the fees derived from this network, with the obligation/cost of providing validation to its users. OmiseGO (OMG) is the Plasma decentralized exchange, hosting an open-source digital wallet platform from Omise, connecting mainstream payments, cross-border remittances, and much more. Fiat & crypto-friendly, cross-chain compatible, Ethereum-powered, and built on plasma.io.

name: Dash
description: Dash is a Scrypt-based fork of LiteCoin. It was originally released as XCoin, then rebranded as Darkcoin before being rebranded again as Dash. Dash developers created several novel blockchain technologies, including a unique hashing algorithm that resists ASIC Mining. It is a privacy-centric cryptocurrency with native transaction mixing capabilities. Users can decide which transactions they want to make untraceable by sending them through the mixing protocol. All other transactions are pseudo anonymous, but still encrypted using the relative security of a blockchain hashing algorithm. ???Dash also features a two-tier hierarchy of nodes that enables instant transaction confirmation

name: Primecoin
description: Primecoin is a proof of work cryptocurrency with a unique proof of work algorithm that finds chains of prime numbers. The purpose behind the creation of primecoin was to provide a proof of work system that can also produce useful output instead of simply throwing away the work done, as in the more popular SHA-256 of Scrypt hashing. Primecoin accepts three types of prime number chains ??"Cunningham Chainof the first kind, Cunningham Chain of the second kind and Bi-twin chain. Some of the largest Cunningham chains have been found by the Primecoin network.

name: Namecoin
description: Namecoin is a protocol based upon the bitcoin protocol but developed for the specific purpose of providing a decentralized DNS and identity system. Namecoin is merge-mined with bitcoin and as such shares its mining properties. Namecoin is most notable for its .bit top level distributed domain system.

name: Loopring
description: Loopring is an open, multilateral token exchange protocol for decentralized exchange on the Ethereum blockchain. Loopring is intended to serve as a common building block with open standards, driving interoperability among decentralized applications (DAPPs) that incorporate exchange functionality. Trades are executed by a system of Ethereum smart contracts that are publicly accessible, free to use, and that any dApp can hook into. Loopring???s token is based on the ERC20 Ethereum Token Standard and can be liquidated through a Loopring smart contract.

name: MaidSafeCoin
description: SafeCoin is the official coin of MaidSafe.net, a project that began in Scotland in 2006 to create a distributed internet using user-donated computing resources. Safecoin incentivizes people to contribute data storage resources to the network; as the network grows, it can handle more traffic and resemble the centralized internet used today. Maidsafe stands for Massive Array of Internet Disks + Secure Access for Everyone. ???In April of 2014, a proxy token, MaidSafeCoin, was launched on top of Mastercoin and distributed through an IPO that raised ~$6 million. ???MaidSafeCoin will be???exchangeable into SafeCoin when MaidSafe launches. ???SafeCoin will be???used to purchase resources on the MaidSafe network.

name: Monaco
description: Monaco is a Ethereum based ERC20 token. The core product is a Monaco VISA??? Card that allows users to simplly pay in Ether or Bitcoin. ???You can spend your Ether or Bitcoin with a physical Monaco VISA??? Card, wherever VISA??? cards are accepted, both online & offline. Only the exact amount that you spend with your Monaco VISA??? Card will be incrementally exchanged from ETH/BTC in real-time when you swipe your card, with rest being securely stored in your wallet to which only you have access. You can Exchange money at perfect interbank exchange rates and send money internationally using Monaco App.

name: FirstBlood
description: FirstBlood is an Ethereum-based digital asset intended for eSports competitions. Oken economics reward players based off in-game skills, tracked via smart contracts and blockchain oracles. FirstBlood wants to make eSports more transparent while introducing more gamers into cryptocurrency mainstream adoption. It offers a decentralized application and its platform is based on the Ethereum Virtual Machine. Players can spend their tokens to begin competitive matches, wager on themselves to win the match, and host tournaments. FirstBlood allows votes to be cast for winners. 30% of the tokens are held by the Yunbi exchange, but no other address owns more than 6%. Current games include Overwatch, Dota 2, but others will be added for compatibility.

name: Bancor
description: The Bancor Protocol is a blockchain-based system for discovery and a liquidity mechanism supporting multiple smart contract platforms. The flexibility of these blockchains allows tokens to be locked in reserve and to issue smart tokens on the Bancor system, enabling anyone to instantly purchase or liquidate the smart token in exchange for any of its reserve tokens. The BNT is the first smart token on the Bancor system and it will hold a single reserve in Ether. Other smart tokens, by using BNT as one of their reserves, connect to the BNT network. The BNT establishes network dynamics where increased demand for any of the network???s smart tokens increases demand for the common BNT, benefiting all other smart tokens holding it in reserve.

name: MobileGo
description: MobileGo is an open-source POW cryptocurrency intended to be primary payment and transaction currency for MobileGo.io, a crypto-centric mobile gaming platform and store. Its crowdsale happened between April to May 20 MobileGo uses a similar UI to Google Play and offers 300 mobile games and seeks to expand to thousands of games. It is designed to compete with the Google Play Store by promising 20% higher revenue shares and 60 hour developer payouts as opposed to Google Play???s 60 day payouts. MobileGo uses GameCredits to pay for in-game transactions and game payments and will be able to run tournaments. There are options for player run tournaments, decentralized P2P match play and virtual item marketplaces. MobileGo???s platform seeks to gamify the platform so users can earn discounts and rewards through playing games. MobileGo wants to benefit game developers, as the platform only takes 10% of the revenue versus 30% taken by Google or Apple. MobileGo allows integrations for SDKs and faster and more frequent updates.There is a 100 million MobileGo total supply, 70 million were released during the crowdsale while 30 million were retained by the MobileGo Foundation. ???

name: Edgeless
description: Edgeless is an Ethereum-based digital asset intended to become an online gambling revolution by resolving the classic trust problem of House Edge. House Edge refers to the mathematical advantage of the gambling game. Edgeless intends to make this process of gambling ???provably fair??? through transparency and cryptography. The Edgeless platform is regulated by smart contracts. The coin provides a blockchain based casino seeking to improve transparency and resolve the issue of cheating players on online casinos, called the House Edge. Edgeless provides 0% House Edge, no logins or registrations, anonymity, and transparent random number fairness.

name: AdEx
description: AdEx is an Ethereum-based digital asset which utilizes smart contracts to offer publishers and advertisers an ability to interact with users. ???It is focused on video advertising. AdEx is a blockchain based ad exchange aimed at disrupting the existing online advertising landscape.The exchange facilitates relationships between publishers, advertisers and end users. Distributed applications connect to users via the AdEx user interface online. The AdEx Platform allows advertisers to buy or sell advertising space and time.

name: Bitquence
description: Bitquence is an Ethereum based ERC20 token. The company wants to create a platform that could provide a single point of interaction with the new economy. This Digital Wallet will be the backbone for Bitquence's asset management and cryptocurrency services platform.

name: Civic
description: Civic is an Ethereum based digital asset that enables businesses and individuals to secure their identity. Civic???s key utility is protect against ID theft. It pays identity verifiers to do necessary KYC work with coin and these results are stored in the blockchain. Their decentralized architecture and mobile device biometrics allow multi-factor authentication without usernames, passwords, third-party authenticators, or physical hardware. Keys are protected in a third-party wallet, identity is fully encrypted, and public identifiers have hashed keys for an authenticating authority.

name: DigixDAO
description: Digix DAO is a new form of cryptographic asset in that it is a Decentralised Autonomous Organisation or DAO for short. DAO are basically Companies written in code that are there to perform a set of functions with holders of the tokens voting in relation to the number of tokens they hold.  The Digix DAO gives users the right to profits in the trading of Digix tokens (DGX) which own the right to gold stored in vault in Singapore. So if people trade 20 gold bars per day - the Digix DAO token holders will have the profits of the commission from those trades distributed equally amongst themselves.

name: Bitdeal
description: Bitdeal is a digital currency that allows two willing parties to conduct safe and private transactions anywhere around the world. Bitdeal is written in a Turing Complete Language while Bitcoin was only written in a stack based language that is not Turing Complete. While Bitcoin, for example, facilitates cash transactions, Bitdeal is a very complex blockchain based contract mechanism. It is not only dedicated to moving and validating money.

name: Basic Attenti...
description: The Basic Attention Token is an Ethereum-based digital asset that powers the blockchain enabled Brave Platform, an internet service that pioneers with applications for advertising and media services. Brave offers a fast, open source, privacy-focused web browser that blocks web trackers, false advertisements, has a built in transactional ledger which captures user behavior. This privately monitored behavior helps derive the name for attention, as user???s attention determines how the platform rewards publishers with BATs. In exchange for using the platform, users receive BATs. Publishers have an incentive to stay on the platform since they receive more revenue because middlemen and fraud are reduced. Users have an incentive to use Brave because they are targeted by fewer but more personally targeted ads which have been checked for the nature of their ads and blocking malvertisements. Advertisers also receive a more clear understanding of the impact of their marketing.

name: Blocknet
description: The Blocknet is founded on the XBridge, the first peer-to-peer protocol enabling communication between nodes on different blockchains. It is open source and is implemented in every Blocknet-enabled app. It is what connects an open-ended array of services ??? either decentralized or centralized ??? to one another.

name: TenX
description: The TenX platform connects assets and businesses on blockchains to the real-world in a decentralized manner. Developers can develop security smart contract modules, businesses can connect their users and use case to real-world payments. TenX offers a debit card and accompanying mobile wallet that can be funded not only with any blockchain asset. A TenX wallet can be used in almost 200 countries at over 36 million points of acceptance. TenX leverages the COMIT Standard, short for Cryptographically-secure Off-chain Multi-asset Instant Transaction network, which works in a processes transactions rapidly and across blockchain assets. The TenX token, PAY, allows users to "own" part of the TenX system, as for every transaction made with the wallet, the token holder receives rewards in Ether. The company has received investments from Fenbushi Capital and ICH. TenX is a payment platform built on top of the Comit Network. The payment platform gets rid of most fees associated with international banking and transfers. The company will offer a physical card and a virtual card that lets you interact with products and services in the real-world.

name: 0x
description: 0x is an open protocol that facilitates the decentralized exchange of Ethereum-based tokens and assets. Developers can use 0x to build their own custom exchange apps with a wide variety of user-facing applications i.e. 0x OTC, a decentralized application that facilitates trustless over-the-counter trading of Ethereum-based tokens.  The 0x token (ZRX) is used by Makers and Takers to pay transaction fees to Relayers (entities that host and maintain public order books). ZRX tokens are also used for decentralized governance over 0x protocol???s update mechanism which allows its underlying smart contracts to be replaced and improved over time.

name: Ethereum Classic
description: Ethereum Classic is the native token of the original Ethereum protocol. ???The Ethereum blockchain hard forked from the original Ethereum Classic blockchain in 2016 because of the DAO hack that drained millions from the Ethereum ecosystem. Ethereum Classic lacks backwards compatibility with the hard forked Ethereum. This means that updates to the chain like Plasma, Byzantium, and the movement from PoW to PoS will not be implemented. To the community, Ethereum Classic supporters are purist who believe the original code is more censorship resistant, immutable, and decentralized than the Ethereum chain.

name: Ark
description: Ark is a cryptocurrency platform built on top an improved Delegated Proof of Stake (DPoS) system derived from Lisk, Crypti, and BitShares. It uses Smart Bridges to communicate with other (new and existing) blockchains to further increase its reach, providing a wider range of features in a single place.  Ark plans to stimulate cryptocurrency mass adoption by offering multiple consumer tools like a card network, game tokens, anonymous transactions, multi-signature accounts, and others. Adding more features and tools along the way.

name: Syscoin
description: SysCoin is a cryptocurrency that seeks to implement a distributed marketplace into the blockchain and add value to financial infrastructures. SysCoin???s network protects business data and also intends to enable brokerage for deeds, wills, trusts, stocks, and bonds over the blockchain through their arbitration system. SysCoin uses a SCRYPT Proof-of-Work consensus algorithm. With every new block, SysCoin uses Kimoto???s Gravity Well (KGW) as an adjustment algorithm to determine the difficulty of each new block. With KGW, a multipool mines for different cryptocurrencies and switches between them in rapid succession, allowing miners to reap higher returns. KGW smoothes out the retargeting of this difficulty allowing for large amounts of computing power to move between networks without causing networking disruptions between timing intervals between mined blocks. SysCoin has 2 billion coins generated in total.

name: Factom
description: Factom is a system for securing millions of real-time records in the blockchain with a single hash. Businesses and governments can use Factom to simplify records management, record business processes, and address security and compliance issues. Factom uses the blockchain to power a remarkable range of applications, including audit systems, medical records, supply chain management, voting systems, property titles, legal applications, and financial systems. Factom claims to be a data layer for the blockchain. It offers three proofs: 1) proof of existence, a document existed in this form at a verified time; 2) proof of process, a document existed and is linked to this new updated document; 3) proof of audit, a document when it changed can be verified to have changed according to a set of rules.

name: Siacoin
description: Sia is an actively developed decentralized storage platform. Users all over the world contribute disk storage from their computers to form a decentralized network. Anybody with Siacoins can rent storage from hosts on Sia. This is accomplish via "smart" storage contracts stored on the Sia blockchain. The smart contract provides a payment to the host only after the host has kept the file for a given amount of time. If the host loses the file, the host does not get paid. The distributed nature of the Sia network enables many optimizations in latency, throughput, reliability, and security. The decentralized nature of the Sia network enables anyone with storage to get paid, lowering the barrier to entry and reducing the overall price of cloud storage.The storage platform itself is still in beta, and only uploads that are 500mb or less in size are supported by the wallet.

name: FairCoin
description: FairCoin is a decentralised cryptocurrency, distributed through an airdrop process in March 2014 . An approximate 49,750 addresses were logged for the giveaway, each able to claim 1000 FAIR per hour. Automated airdrop claiming methods had no effect, as each IP address could register once per hour, and 2 different captchas had to be solved. FairCoin's distribution method allowed a good portion of the cryptocurrency community to claim a little bit of the 50,000,000 FairCoins, each. All the coins were premined and fairly distributed to thousands from all over the world.

name: DigiByte
description: DigiByte (DGB) is a worldwide decentralized payment network & digital currency, inspired by Bitcoin. DigiByte allows you to move money over the internet similar to PayPal & Western Union but with many improvements, including lightning fast transactions with minimal or no fees.

name: Aeternity
description: Aeternity is a scalable blockchain platform that enables high bandwidth transacting, purely-functional smart contracts, and decentralized oracles.  The use of the blockchain is not free, and requires that the user spends a token called Aeon. Aeon's are used as payment for any resources one consumes on the platform, as well as the basis for financial applications implemented on the platform. All system fees get paid with aeon, all smart contracts settle in aeon.

name: Wings
description: Wings is a platform where users can create and invest in Decentralized Autonomous Organizations (DAOs). These DAOs can be created without any specific coding knowledge or technical skills, and are approved through a prediction market feature. the Wings Platform is run by a DAO itself, the Wings DAO. Wings DAO tokens, WINGS, represent a share within that DAO and allows users to vote on the developments of the platform, and to recieve dividends from the fees generated within the platform.

name: Bitcoin
description: Bitcoin is the first true digital peer to peer currency system that ushered in the era of cryptocurrency and related technologies. Bitcoin was announced by Satoshi Nakamoto in November 2008 and the first block was mined in January 2009. It???s code has been forked and used directly or indirectly for most of the other cryptocurrencies. Even when the code is not directly forked, Bitcoin has formed the basis of almost every other cryptocurrency in existence. Bitcoin is described in the original whitepaper as ???A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System???.

name: Byteball Bytes
description: Byteball is a decentralized database with it's own native cryptocurrency, Bytes, that unlike most does not require PoW or PoS mining and does not have a blockchain nor blocks. Instead, Byteball links transactions by signing the hashes from the previous transactions on the new one. These links between transactions form a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph). Since Byteball has no blocks, there is no block size issue. Byteball can be used as a means to transfer value between users in a transaction, either with Bytes or assets that can be issued on the network or as a decentralized database that allows users to store information within it. Byteball's currency, Bytes, are used to pay transaction fees in this network. Transactions can be meant to exchange value or to store any type of data. The transaction fees (Bytes) are relative to the Bytes used in the transaction, so if a transaction uses 500 Bytes, that's the tx fee that will be charged. This system gives the currency intrinsic value, each Byte is worth a byte of information that is stored on the network, which allows the system to scale according to its use.

name: Stellar Lumens
description: Stellar???s mission is to expand financial access and literacy worldwide. Stellar was initially a fork of Ripple???and was founded by Jeb McCaleb, one of Ripple???s co-founders???to serve as an open-source network for handling currency transfers over a blockchain. Stellar???s ledger serves as a marketplace for offers of currency exchange by matching buyers and sellers and using crypto currencies as intermediary values when needed. Near zero transaction fees on the network facilitate affordable remittance transfers and cost effective micropayments. Stellar helps resources, such as air time minutes, function more like currency by making transactions frictionless.Stellar coins are called Lumens.

name: I/O Coin
description: I0coin has a good combination of transaction speed and security. 90 second confirmations make for quick transactions, so you can get on with your life. Network mining power ranked in the top 5% means your coins are super secure, for your peace of mind. I "zero" coin. Zero premine. Zero inflation by 2018. Zero gimmicks. I0coin doesn't play games with your money.

name: TokenCard
description: The TokenCard is a project that focuses on providing an easy method for users to interact and secure their tokens. It allows users to keep their Ethereum-based tokens secure and under user-set spending and security parameters through the Token Contract Wallet. The tokens can be spend through the physical TokenCard, enabling online payments, PoS transactions and ATM withdrawals. The TokenCard token is also an Ethereum-based asset, holding a pro-rata claim on the TKN Asset Contract. This Asset Contract accrues a 1% licensing fee (enforced by smart contracts) on all TokenCard transactions. At any time, TKN holders can redeem their share of the underlying assets by 'cashing and burning' the TKN tokens.

name: Particl
description: Particl is an open source blockchain-based eCommerce platform, allowing customers and merchants to be directly connected on a peer-to-peer network with reliable privacy features. Users can buy or sell anything, similar to eBay, Etsy or Amazon, except that all the transaction data, payments and conversations happen over a self-governed, distributed network instead of a central server. Transactions within the network are conducted in PART, the native cryptocurrency in the Particle PoS blockchain.

name: Lisk
description: Lisk is an open source cryptocurrency that can exchange value ecosystem launched in 2016. It intends to be a JavaScript based platform that can deploy blockchain applications, similar to Ethereum. Lisk is a fork of Crypti and launched with an ICO and was the 2nd most successful crowsale at the time, Waves and the DAO would surpass it. For a brief tie, Lisk became the second most traded cryptocurrency traded after Bitcoin. Lisk intends for its blockchain applications are run on sidechains to help with scalability issues. 101 master nodes operate using a Delegated Proof of Stake consensus mechanism in order to process side chains to synchronize with the main chain. The DPoS used by Lisk was pioneered by Bitshares, however only the top 101 delegates determined by voting weight are forging and securing the transactional ledger. Lisk integrated into Microsoft???s Blockchain as a Service platform.

name: Waves
description: Waves are the native digital asset of the Waves Platform, a blockchain ecosystem that uses proof of stake consensus founded in 2016. Waves propose a PoS upgrade called Leased Proof of Stake (LPoS) that aims to increase transaction throughput and decrease transaction times. The Waves ecosystem is has a virtual machine that allows developers to deploy smart contracts on the Waves blockchain. Developers can develop and deploy cryptocurrencies, similar to the ERC20 token built on Ethereum, on the Waves client.

name: Rise
description: RISE is a Lisk-based digital asset intended to serve as a transactional currency for creating and deploying Decentralized Applications, Smart Contracts, Side Chain, and digital assets. The RISE ICO launched in 2016 with a total supply of 100 milion coins. RISE uses a Delegated Proof of Stake consensus mechanism. The Lisk code base enables GUIs and security to be applied across these creations. RISE???s SDKs enable development support for several languages.

name: Decred
description: Decred is an open source cryptocurrency launched in February 2016. Created by original Bitcoin developers who envisioned a cryptocurrency that wouldn???t be susceptible to the mining oligarchies. The purpose of the cryptocurrency is to serve as a secure medium of transaction and enable an autonomous and self-ruling ecosystem where stakeholders rule through decentralization. disintermediation, and privacy. Created in the in the spirit of open participation, everyone can join and contribute. They are pushing forward a consensus voting model with their politeia proposal system, voting process. Decred uses an innovative hybrid proof-of-work and proof-of-stake consensus mechanism. Proof-of-Work mining is used to validate transactions, while Proof-of-Stake mining is used to vote on network development. They offer smart contracts like the Lightning Network, cross-chain atomic swaps between different cryptocurrencies, and cross-platform wallets. These are wallet apps that support Windows, macOS, and Linux.

name: Steem
description: Steem tokens are the digital asset built atop the Steem.it ecosystem which serves as a blockchain-based social media platform. The Steem ecosystem uses a PoW consensus mechanism, with mining rewards going to content creators and to fund future. Steem tokens are used as the platform???s medium of exchange for posting high quality and relevant content, and circulating and deciding on the publicity of content through a post-upvoting mechanism. The protocol introduces three cryptocurrencies: within the Steemit ecosystem: Steem, Steem Power (SP), used to receive interest from user holdings and allows for greater user revenue, and Steem Backed Dollars (SBD), which protect the originality of the holding. Steem tokens are liquid and purchasable through exchanges, these tokens can then be converted into SP or SBD. SP is illiquid for a 3 month vesting fund period. Upvoting content on the Steem.it platform depletes a user???s SP. Owning more SP allows a participant to earn more revenue than he or she would otherwise generate for in SP. SBD protects content creators from volatility and can be exchanged for USD.

name: Bytecoin
description: Bytecoin is an open-source P2P cryptocurrency launched in July 2012 intended for untraceable cash settlements. Bytecoin was the first cryptocurrency based on the CryptoNote application layer and seeks to increase privacy for individuals and minimize risks for businesses using SHA-256 encryption. Bytecoin was created independently from Bitcoin blockchain technology with Java, but was rewritten in 2013 with C++. In 2015, a number of improvements for payment gateways, API layers for integration with software, and blockchain-based application support with aliases systems, assets, and embedded turing-complete language were developed. Its Proof-of-Work computer algorithm differs from Bitcoin in a way that makes mining with GPU less efficient than Bitcoin, because of its AES command system for x86 microprocessors and memory. Bytecoin claims to allow for unlimited instant international payments, secure crypto algorithms require intense electricity and computing power to override, and securitization of personal data. There are 50 coins per block.

name: Aeon
description: AEON is a private, secure, untraceable currency. ???AEON uses a cryptographically sound system to allow you to send and receive funds without your transactions being easily revealed on the blockchain. This ensures that your purchases, receipts, and all transfers remain absolutely private by default. Individual wallets have a 24 word mnemonic that is only displayed once, and can be written down to backup the wallet. Wallet files are encrypted with a passphrase to ensure they are useless if stolen. By taking advantage of ring signatures, a special property of certain types of cryptography, AEON is able to ensure that transactions are not only untraceable, but have an optional measure of ambiguity that ensures that transactions cannot easily be tied back to an individual user or computer.

name: Energycoin
description: EnergyCoin (ENRG) is a pure PoS scrypt altcoin with an initial distribution of 110,000,000 coins going to the 2,000 members of the community. EnergyCoin is a decentralized and green cryptocurrency, with PoE (Prove of Environment) concept. EnergyCoin is one of the long-standing PoS altcoins and has been around since April 2014. The PoS annualised rates drop by 2% per year from 10% to 2% in year 5 - thereafter at year six there is a fixed interest rate of 1% per annum. There is a thirty second block time and a difficulty retargeting each block.

name: Tether
description: Tether is a next generation financial platform powered by the Bitcoin blockchain. USDT is a cryptocurrency asset issued on the Bitcoin blockchain via the Omni Layer Protocol. Each USDT unit is backed by a U.S Dollar held in the reserves of the Tether Limited and can be redeemed through the Tether Platform. USDT can be transferred, stored, spent, just like bitcoins or any other cryptocurrency. USDT and other Tether currencies were created to facilitate the transfer of national currencies, to provide users with a stable alternative to Bitcoin and to provide an alternative for exchange and wallet audits which are currently unreliable. USDT provides an alternative to Proof of Solvency methods by introducing a Proof of Reserves Process. In the Tether Proof of Reserves system, the amount of USDT in circulations can be easily checked on the Bitcoin blockchain via the tools provided at Omnichest.info, while the corresponding total amount of USD held reserves is proved by publishing the bank balance and undergoing periodic audits by professionals.

name: Gas
description: GAS is the cryptocurrency on top of the NEO blockchain ecosystem used to fund ICOs. Formerly referred to as a Antcoins and Antshares, GAS works in kind with NEO as a cryptocurrency atop the NEO platform. Demand for GAS is driven up over time by keeping it scarce. Demand GAS has been ignored for NEO, which has driven up the price for GAS. There are two built-in system assets: NEO and GAS. NEO represent the ownership of the blockchain, which is used for electoral accounting, to obtain GAS dividends, etc. GAS represents the right to use the blockchain, and are used to pay fees of various systems on the chain.

name: Kin
description: The Kin token is an Ethereum-based cryptocurrency that is to be used for daily online activities such as instant messaging, social media, tipping and payments within the Kin Ecosystem. Kin is the digital token launched by Kik to serve a number of decentralized applications. Kin can also serve as a medium for exchange with other services.

name: EOS
description: EOS tokens are ERC-20 compatible tokens distributed on the Ethereum blockchain. EOS.IO is software that introduces a blockchain architecture designed to enable vertical and horizontal scaling of decentralized applications.. This is achieved through an operating system-like construct upon which applications can be built. The software provides accounts, authentication, databases, asynchronous communication and the scheduling of applications across multiple CPU cores and/or clusters. The resulting technology is a blockchain architecture that has the potential to scale to millions of transactions per second, eliminates user fees and allows for quick and easy deployment of decentralized applications.

name: Status
description: The Status Network Token is an open-source Ethereum-based cryptocurrency required to interact with the Status Networ whcich intends to serve as a decenralized messaging platform. Status also seeks to perform roles as a mobile internet browser and payment system which allows users to trade their Status tokens in exchange for digital assets on the Ethereum blockchain. Status allows users to control the data surrounding their identity. Status integrates with other digital identity blockchain enabled applications like uPort, Gnosis, Aragon, Oasis Exchange, Ethlance, Ethersic, and Ujo.

name: Ardor
description: Ardor coins are a NXT-based digital asset enabling users to stake ownership of their Blockchain as a Service Platform that allows users to create child chains with their own tokens. These child chains allow the creators to customize the issuance process for those assets. Ardor is developed by Jelurida, the company that created the NXT Proof-of-Stake blockchain protocol, and is intended to serve as an evolution over the NXT blockchain. Main Chain Ardor tokens are used in recording transactions, forge tokens originate from the transaction fees, the mining equivalent. Ardor assets are able to access all mainchain features like shuffling, asset creation and trading, aliasing, secure messaging, voting, and phasing.

name: Hshare
description: Hshare is a dual network blockchain comprised both of a blockchain-based network and a DAG-based network. It allows for anonymous transactions through the use of zero proof technology. The blockchain-based side of Hshare features a PoW/PoS cryptocurrency.

name: Walton
description: Walton Coin is a Chinese Ethereum-based digital asset associated with the Waltonchain ecosystem that intends to combine RFID and blockchain technology to help decentralize supply chains. RFID readers become a node on the chain. This hardware prevents bottlenecking in commercial applications. It adds key values to securitization of supply chains, traceability back to sources, anti-counterfeiting, and reduced labor costs. Walton consists of the Walton protocol, the Waltonchain software system, and the Walton Coin. There is a constant total supply of 100 million million Walton Coins. It adds functionality for issuing sub chains, credit and mortgage systems, dividend interests, distributed asset exchanges, and distributed governance models. RFIDs can be associated for each product to record the processing of manufactured consumer goods. The physical hardware tag chips contain a hash value of the gag???s status and critical data ensuring a tamper-resistant state. In January 2018, there will be a conversion from an ERC20 to a WTC token.

name: ChainLink
description: ChainLink is a blockchain-base middleware, acting as a bridge between cryptocurrency smart contracts and off-chain resources like data feeds, various web APIs, and traditional bank account payments. This way, ChainLink allows Smart Contracts to communicate with external resources on their own. LINK is an ERC20 token based on the Ethereum Blockchain. It is used to pay ChainLink Node operators for the retrieval of data from off-chain data feeds, formatting of data into blockchain readable formats, off-chain computation, and uptime guarantees they provide as operators.

name: Populous
description: Populous is an Ethereum-based ERC20 token is an invoice and trade finance platform built on the Ethereum network. Populous uses XBRL, Z Score formula, Smart Contracts, Stable tokens and other technologies in the cryptoshpere to create a unique trading environment for investors and invoice sellers. Because Populous is built on the Ethereum Virtual Machine, the platform enables anyone to participate in an alternative finance marketplace which is currently available only to banks, financial institutions, wealthy individuals, family offices and governments. So by allowing investors to use cryptocurrency on the platform, investors from any part of the world, can invest in an invoice sold buy an invoice seller from any part of the world. For example a investor from China or Japan can invest in invoices sold buy UK businesses and vice versa. In order to create a stable trading environment, Populous is pegged token which are Ethereum ERC 20 token standard.

name: FunFair
description: FunFair is an Ethereum-based digital asset with an ICO launched in June 2017 that intends to build an online gaming platform. FunFair establishes a decentralized model for 3D games to be played and built in HTML5. FUN coin is used for betting, lending, paying out players, and compensating stakeholders. Supply is fixed, the total number of tokens was determined and locked at the end of the token creation event. It utilizes Fate Channels, off-chain channels that quickly process each transaction. Odds are transparent and publicly auditable to ensure fairness. This platform can be licensed to online casinos and companies as a backend solution. Tokens are burned with each transaction.

name: Dogecoin
description: If someone launches a digital coin based off an internet dog meme, is it an avante-garde media experiment, a joke, or a real currency? Enter Dogecoin, a cryptocurrency protocol based on Litecoin and inspired by theDoge internet memeof the Japanese Shiba Inu dog. When it launched, Dogecoin had already accumulated a significant internet following. At the time, it was seen as a counter-balance to the fraud-plagued and Silk-Road-associated Bitcoin. It was a coin for everyone. However, it hit choppy waters in 2014, when concerns that the coin had been co-opted by a company looking to pump up its impending investment rounds.Ultimately, DogeCoin???s resilience has surprised many. The ability of the coin to stay in circulation with such incredibly small exchange rates attests to its popularity as a currency, a movement, and a meme itself ??? even in the midst of controversy.

name: Gnosis
description: Gnosis provides an open-source Ethereum-based ERC20 digital asset that intends to become a decentralized prediction market. It provides a gamified platform to predict the outcome of any event with applications everything from financial markets. In particular, it seeks to create a non-monetized prediction market for securities research firms to get outside feedback on expected stock fundamentals. Gnosis is backed by ConsenSys. Gnosis interacts with WIZ, an ERC20 token used on the platform generated from GNO. It is possible to lock down GNO for a specified time in exchange for receiving WIZ through emission contracts. WIZ is used for trading fees, speculating on events, creating markets, subsidizing markets, and participating in those markets for a fee. GNO tokens function as WIZ fee credit generation machines. The amount of WIZ generated for GNO does not decrease even if activity decreases.

name: Kyber Network
description: Kyber Network is a blockchain exchange(ZRX). Kyber Network aims to allow users to hold their current coins in their own personal wallets and to do a transaction on an exchange using smart contracts. Transactions are be instant with a single confirmation. Kyber Network will have liquidity allowing for instant transactions. Kyber Network never holds users funds everything is done on smart contracts. High Liquidity: Kyber Network will maintain a reserve of tokens to provide high liquidity so you can get your tokens instantly when you trade. Instant Trade: There???s no waiting for confirmation and no deposit required. You can instantly get your tokens once your transaction is included in the blockchain. Kyber Network is an on-chain protocol which allows instant exchange and conversion of digital assets (e.g. crypto tokens) and cryptocurrencies (e.g. Ether, Bitcoin, ZCash) with high liquidity. KyberNetwork wants to implement several ideal operating properties of an exchange including trustless, decentralized execution, instant trade and high liquidity. Besides serving as an exchange, KyberNetwork also provides payment APIs that will allow Ethereum accounts to easily receive payments from any crypto tokens.

name: Bitcoin Cash
description: Bitcoin Cash (BCH/BCC) is a hard fork of the cryptocurrency bitcoin. The fork occurred on August 1, 2017. On July 20, 2017, the bitcoin miners voted, 97% in favor, on the Bitcoin Improvement Proposal (BIP) 91. The proposal, by Bitmain Warranty engineer James Hilliard, was to activate Segregated Witness (SegWit). Block 478558 was the last common block and thus the first Bitcoin Cash block was 478559. Bitcoin Cash cryptocurrency wallet started to reject BTC block and BTC transactions since 13:20 UTC, Aug 1st 2017 because it used a timer to initiate a fork. It implements a block size increase to 8 MB. Even though the fork allows for a higher block size, block generation was so sporadic that the original chain was 920 MB bigger than the chain of the fork, as of 9 August 2017. Due to the new "Emergency Difficulty Adjustment" algorithm used by Bitcoin Cash, mining difficulty has fluctuated rapidly, and the most profitable chain to mine has thus switched repeatedly between Cash and original Bitcoin. As both chains use the same proof-of-work algorithm, miners can easily move their hashpower between the two. It is important to note that while the alphanumeric address style is the same as the original Bitcoin (BTC), that Bitcoin Cash (BCH/BCC) should not be sent to a Bitcoin (BTC) address. The coins will be irreversibly lost if sent to the wrong wallet type. Like the original Bitcoin, Bitcoin Cash addresses can be used more than once, but should not be reused if privacy is a concern.

name: Qtum
description: Qtum (pronounced ???Quantum???) is a blockchain platform with turing-complete smart contract functionalities while still maintaining a an Unspent Transaction Output (UTXO) transaction model. Decentralized applications (dApps) can be deployed on the Qtum blockchain similar to other ecosystem protocols. Qtum employs a Proof of Stake consensus mechanism. QTUM is the underlying value token in the Qtum blockchain. Qtum aims to solve the underlying problems present in proof of work blockchain ecosystem like Ethereum by implementing proof of stake.

name: Zcash
description: ZCash is a privacy driven cryptocurrency. It uses the Equihash as an algorithm, which is an asymmetric memory-hard Proof of Work algorithm based on the generalized birthday problem. It relies on high RAM requirements to bottleneck the generation of proofs and making ASIC development unfeasible. ZCash uses ???zero-knowledge Succinct Non-interactive Arguments of Knowledge (zk-SNARKs) to ensure that all information (sender, receiver, amount) is encrypted, without the possibility of double-spending. The only information that is revealed regarding transactions is the time in which they take place. The founder and CEO of Zcash is Zooko Wilcox-O'Hearn. Its founding team includes cryptographer Matthew D. Green from Johns Hopkins University. ???Zcash payments are published on a public blockchain, but users are able to use an optional privacy feature to conceal the sender, recipient, and amount being transacted. Like Bitcoin, Zcash has a fixed total supply of 21 million units. In the first 4 years, 20 % of the coins are transferred to a "founders reward", via a multisignature wallet. Zcash affords private transactors the option of "selective disclosure", allowing a user to prove payment for auditing purposes. One such reason is to allow private transactors the choice to comply with anti-money laundering or tax regulations. "Transactions are auditable but disclosure is under the participant's control.???

name: Centra
description: Centra Tech has designed a multi-blockchain debit card that connects to a smart wallet that aims to be safe, secure, and insured. Centra currently supports 8+ major cryptocurrencies: Bitcoin, Ethereum, ERC20 Tokens, Litecoin, Ripple, Dash, Zcash, & Monero with more to come. Centra team designed a platform to create a global account solution for anyone who lack banking resources. Centra Tech is also launching a platform called Coin Bay (www.cBay.io) which will be the world's first Amazon style store that is designed to be cryptocurrency acceptable.

name: IOTA
description: IOTA introduces an open-source distributed ledger protocol that seeks to implement a blockless ecosystem called the Tangle. It is intended to be a quantum-resistant Direct Acyclic Graph ledger. IOTA???s digital currency has a fixed money supply with zero inflationary costs. It offers zero-fee transactions and no fixed limits on transactions per second. Scaling grows with increasing returns to scale through verifying two previous transactions on the blockchain. NIOTA has no separation between users and validators and validation is an intrinsic property. The key utility of this is focused on IoT and machine-to-machine economies that ensure the integrity of large scale micro and nanopayments. The Tangle remains experimental and requires large scale implementation of chips required at the bottom connectivity layer of the technical stack.

name: Golem
description: The Golem Network is a decentralized computation network. Using Golem users can buy or sell computational power from other users in a peer to peer environment. Golem is built using Ethereum smart contracts as a transaction system for nano-payments within the network. Golem Network Tokens (GNT) will serve as a secure medium for all transactions within the Golem Network.

name: BitConnect
description: BitConnect Coin is Toronto based startup founded in 2013 that uses a Proof of Work Scrypt cryptocurrency. They are used by bitconnect community members for bitconnect services and to store and invest the wealth in a non-government controlled currency. The BitConnect coins will also be used as payment system on number of BitConnect partner websites. BitConnect???s economic model is based on network effect for mass adoption by rewarding their users that brings more users onto the system. ???In exchange for staking Bitcoin in the system for a set amount of time, users are rewarded a payout of the BitConnect token. Based on a clearly present pyramid structure, most believe this a ponzi scheme. ??????

name: Komodo
description: Komodo is a privacy cryptocurrency that is a fork of Zcash built on a new consensus mechanism, called Delayed Proof of Work. This consensus mechanism combines the Bitcoin protocol and its associated security with zero knowledge proof anonymity. DPoW allow the Komodo team to audit the Bitcoin blockchain. Komodo is issued through the Equihash PoW, popularized by Zcash. Like in a Delegated Proof of Stake system, new block information is first sent through a preset selection of nodes. Customized transactions are inserted onto the Bitcoin blockchain from Komodo???s process. In order to hack this system, the hacker is required to rewrite both chains. Komodo introduces decentralized ICOs by providing privacy focused P2p ICO mechanisms incorporating zk-SNARK technology through their system BarterDEX. Komodo seeks to introduce BarterDex to atomic swaps in order to increase the volume and liquidity without compromising decentralization while solving the problem of order matching and funding.

name: Ripple
description: Ripple is a cryptocurrency that intends to serve as the medium of exchange for international financial transactions at a lower cost. Ripple seeks to connect banks payment providers, corporations, and cryptocurrency exchanges through a frictionless method. Ripple is teamed up with American Express and Santander to implement their solution globally. Ripple seeks to complement Bitcoin by serving as a distributed P2P network to resolve systemic risk in international transaction. Each transaction burns a small bit of Ripple in the process. Ripple has several financial institutions as paying customers, and they provide RippleNet to serve as their API.

name: Ubiq
description: Ubiq is an ecosystem token, forked of Ethereum, that seeks to become a decentralized platform for creating smart contracts and decentralized applications. Uibq??????s platform enables third parties to carry out tasks and automate solutions adjusted consensus mining difficulty by using Digibyte???s Digishield v3 algorithm, one also chosen by the Zcash team. Ubiq is an enterprise ready build of the Ethereum blockchain. During the ICO, no Ubiq coins were given to the the development team. The team is led y Julian Yap, one of the ode auditors fo rthe Bittrex exchange. Ubiq codebase serves as an ecosystem for other digital assets, APX, Qwark, and Signum are significant Ubiq projects.

name: SolarCoin
description: SolarCoin (SOLAR) is a coin to increase the adoption and reward photovoltaic power production. The coin is a scrypt Proof of Work cryptocurrency with a block time of 60 seconds. The initial 100 block reward halves every year and the difficulty adjusts every 1440 blocks. The supply of SolarCoin is designed to last 40 years delivering incentives for generating 97,500 TWh of solar electricity. SolarCoin is backed by two forms of proof of work. One is the traditional cryptographic proof of work associated with digital currency. The other proof of work is a 3rd party verified meter reading representing 1 MWh of generated solar electricity. SolarCoin is equitably distributed using both of these proofs of work as a means to reward solar electricity production. SolarCoin can be claimed by individuals living in homes with Solar Energy panels on their roof or large solar electricity farms (leased or financed).

name: Elastic
description: Elastic is an open-source project that provides the infrastructure for a decentralized supercomputers. It is designed to carry out arbitrary tasks over the internet. Those who need computational resources, model their problem using Elastic???s programming language (Elastic PL) and broadcast it on the network, along with a certain amount of XEL coins. The Elastic miners are then motivated to offer their computational resources in exchange for a portion of those XEL coins. Elastic offers potential buyers a large parallel computation cluster composed of many CPUs and GPUs supplied by the miners. The network is ???powered by its own PoW cryptocurrency (XEL) and provides a market-based mechanism to buy and sell computational resources.

name: FirstCoin
description: FirstCoin is a PoW/PoS hybrid blockchain platform that uses the Scrypt algorithm. Next-generation digital currency inspired by the success of Bitcoin. FirstCoin is an alternative digital currency that differs from Bitcoin, characterized by faster transactions. Our goal is to use FirstCoin to connect, coordinate, and support startups showing great potential. Under the FirstCoin aegis, project participants receive varying shares of sharing economy and crowdfunding company successes. Firstcoin simulates the value adding limitation of gold. At most 110 million can be mined, so it cannot inflate like real currency, which countries have a tendency to print in large quantities.

name: NAV Coin
description: NAV Coin is an open-source privacy cryptocurrency which uses a hybrid PoW/PoS consensus mechanism. NAV???s x13 hashing algorithm and encryption software randomizes transaction data, thus dissociating a transaction from its IP address. Links between senders and receivers of money and their IP addresses are then completely destroyed. It scatters transactions across multiple blocks with only marginal delay times to protect senders and receivers. Fragments are molded together before being split so that multiple identical transactions are logged on the network. NAV Coin uses a subchain to to process these transactions. The subchain has no single point of failure, as nodes in the mesh network are able to run independently of the main chain. NAV Coin transactions have 30 second block times and a 20 MB block size. NAV wallets allow users to receive up to 5% interest. NavPI is an open source project running on Raspberry PI boards that can be used to store coins in an environmentally friendly manner.

name: Lykke
description: Lykke is a semi-decentralized trading platform with zero fees for all assets and financial instruments. The platform is based on blockchain technology. The LKK token is a Colored Coin representing shares in the Lykke exchange. Lykke will create a single global marketplace, where any sort of financial instrument can be traded and settled peer to peer with second-by-second interest payments. Unlike the structure of prevailing markets, Lykke will be a level playing field to which anyone with an Internet connection can have access. Lykke???s marketplace utilizes the blockchain pioneered by Bitcoin to offer immediate settlement and direct ownership. All the software will be developed in open source.

name: PIVX
description: PVIX is a privacy cryptocurrency that anonymizes its transactions through Obfuscation and has fast, guaranteed zero confirmation transactions called SwiftTx. PIVX uses a Proof-of-Stake decentralized blockchain voting consensus based on Masternode technology that are secured with a collateral of 10,000 PIVXX. ???Masternodes process Obfuscation, a coin mixing strategy to increase transaction privacy, speed of transactions, and decentralized budgeting for immutable proposals and voting systems.

name: Vertcoin
description: Vertcoin, released on January 11th, 2014, is a cryptocurrency designed to resist the advent of both custom mining hardware and of multipool mining. Vertcoin employs a Scrypt-Adaptive-Nfactor hashing algorithm to provide resistance against application specific integrated circuits (ASICs).

name: Novacoin
description: Novacoin is a Scrypt-based clone of Litecoin. Released on October 1st, 2012, Novacoin implements a hybrid proof of work and proof of stake based approach to coin minting and transaction processing.

name: Nxt
description: NXT is one of the few currencies written from scratch, and in many ways, isn???t a currency per se but a currency code base. NXT???s founder encouraged users to create new currencies on top of it, and its software can be accessed via a web browser and run on smartphones or any device with a Rasberry Pi. Nonetheless, Nxt does have many currency-like features and it trades like other cryptocurrencies.

name: BitcoinDark
description: Bitcoin Dark (BTCD) is a PoW and PoS hybrid alternatve crypto currency based on the same algorithm as Bitcoin itself - SHA256 - the difference is in the intent behind development - where Bitcoin is moving towards regulatory approval with increased transparency, BitcoinDark tries to push further of the belief of decentralisation and anonymity. The block time is 60 seconds - there was a 1.5 premine and a total of 22 million coins are scheduled to be produced.  Following the announcement of the Komodo Platform by the SuperNet team, BitcoinDark could be swapped for KMD coins and will be so until 2018. BTCD technology will be further advanced in the KMD platform.

name: Monero
description: Monero (literally ???coin??? in Esperanto) is a crytpocurrency focused onprivacy,decentralizationandscalability. It was launched as a fork ofByteCoin and uses its CryptoNote codebase and a memory-hard proof of work (POW) consensus mechanism. CryptoNote employs several schemes to make transaction anonymous and untraceable, though unlike other privacy-centric coins, it does not use zero-knowledge proofs. Monero???s memory-hard cryptographic function makes it highly resistant to ASIC mining.

name: NEO
description: NEO is a Chinese-based cryptocurrency that intends to automate the management of digital assets using smart contracts to automate the management of digital assets through smart contracts. Founded in 2014 under the name Antshares, NEO seeks to create a smart economy. A key objective for NEO is to digitize these multiple types of assets, tie them to identities, the register, trade, and circulate multiple types of assets. NEO implements a compatible PKI X.509 standard certificate issuance model. NeoContract???s system enables developers to deploy their smart contracts. Neo???s Lightweight Virtual Machine, NeoVM, has high scalability. NEO has a fixed total supply of 100 million tokens. In 2005, China passed a law called the ???Digital Signature Act,??? similar to the ESIGN act passed 2000 by the US federal government. This act enabled the legally binding structure for digital signatures within contract law. NEO introduces a consensus mechanism that allows the system to resist the Byzantine General???s problem, called Delegated Byzantine Fault Tolerance. A few apps include NeoX, a cross chain system, NeoFS, a decentralized storage solution, and NeoQ, a quantum-proof cryptographic mechanism. Onchain is the Shanghai based blockchain development lab behind the creation of NEO and are pushing Distributed Network Architecture (DNA).

name: Nexus
description: Nexus is a cryptocurrency that is based within a forked Bitcoin a combined PoW and a Nexus Proof of Stake (nPoS) consensus mechanism to provide an alternative to the international banking system. ???Nexus improves on the Bitcoin cryptocurrency by using a multi-threaded balanced messaging protocol. Nexus ???improves on current Bitcoin parameters and resolves one of the most frustrating aspects of cryptocurrency transfers, sending Bitcoin to an invalid address or accidentally sending it to the wrong address, Nexus offers an ability to require a sender and receiver signature, meaning that if Nexus is sent to an invalid address, it does not receive a signature, and will be returned to the sender instead of lost. If a sender realizers this incorrect address after transaction, the sender has a definable period of time to cancel the transfer. If on the receiving side and want to refuse a transfer, it is possible to return it. Nexus uses a SK-1024 hash for block generation used by both CPU and GPU miners to create new blocks versus Bitcoin which uses SHA2, SK-256 bit output, meaning Nexus is four times as secure. It also uses 571 bit private keys, a government recommended standard proposed by NIST and by the NSA. Nexus also introduces three network channels from GPU mining, CPU mining, and nPoS. Thus, a 51% attack must be successful across three channels instead of just one channel with Bitcoin.

name: Augur
description: Augur is an Ethereum-based digital asset intended to serve as a decentralized prediction market to crowdsource analysis. Users create markets for specific questions and profit from trading orders. For specific markets, share prices will vary by changes of the associated probability with that event. Augur???s first contract was launched to the Ethereum network in April 2015 with the Alpha product released shortly after. Augur will see heavy use for political and celebrity betting. Betting outcomes are verified by the community and users are paid when the outcome of an event is verified. Three kinds of tokens are planned including Bitcoin for transactions which could be substituted for a unique internal currency, tradable reputation tokens which measures participant???s reliability scores and predicting outcomes and doubles as a funding source for Augur, and a token which can be used for long term prediction and act with seniority as in a hedge against variations against Bitcoin or the internal currencies.

name: Bytom
description: Bytom is an interactive protocol of multiple byte assets. BTM is currently an Ethereum-based token.

name: Megacoin
description: Megacoin is a Scrypt-based cryptocurrency that is based upon Bitcoin???s code. It also implemented novel code that has since been adopted by most alternative cryptocurrencies. Dr. Kimoto Chan, when he released Megacoin on May 29th, 2013, introduced ???Kimoto???s Gravity Well??? (KGW) which protects smaller networks from the negative effects of smart mining pools that had switch large amounts of hashing power between the networks of different cryptocurrencies. Prior to KGW, alternative cryptocurrencies could be mined temporarily by large pools, raising the difficulty without a corresponding sustained increase in hashing power. This would result in very slow block confirmation times. KGW is a difficulty retargeting algorithm that addresses this issue and prevents such slowdowns.

name: NEM
description: ???NEM is a movement that aims to empower individuals by creating a new economy based on the principles of decentralization, financial freedom, and equality of opportunity.??? ??? NEM Technical ReferenceNEM is a Java-based cryptocurrency announced in 2014 and launched in 2015. It introduced a new consensus mechanism called Proof of Importance (PoI), designed to reward users??? contribution to the NEM community. It is roughly based on proof-of-stake, but it also reflects how active a user is in transacting with other users. NEM also implemented a method of guarding against potentially colluding nodes. Finally, NEM uses a Supernode system that rewards high performing nodes that pass a variety of tests. The founders have also said that one of NEM???s goals is to address wealth inequality, a feature of both existing cryptocurrencies and the ???old economy.??? NEM is theNewEconomyMovement.

name: Ethereum
description: Ethereum was the first cryptocurrency which featured a Turing-complete programming language to execute smart contracts on a blockchain. It is one of the most ambitious ???Bitcoin 2.0??? technologies. The ethereum team introduced several new technologies to blockchain tech that have made it one of the most successful projects out there. Most significantly, the programming language Solidity allows developers to write code for complex transactions that aren???t supported by the Bitcoin protocol. Ethereum also uses a custom hashing algorithm called Ethash that is ASIC resistant.Due in a large part to their smart contract technology, ethereum has become a popular platform to build Dapps, DAOs and launch meta-tokens.

name: DAS
description: Dash is a Scrypt-based fork of LiteCoin. It was originally released as XCoin, then rebranded as Darkcoin before being rebranded again as Dash. Dash developers created several novel blockchain technologies, including a unique hashing algorithm that resists ASIC Mining. It is a privacy-centric cryptocurrency with native transaction mixing capabilities. Users can decide which transactions they want to make untraceable by sending them through the mixing protocol. All other transactions are pseudo anonymous, but still encrypted using the relative security of a blockchain hashing algorithm. ? Dash also features a two-tier hierarchy of nodes that enables instant transaction confirmation

name: Verge
description: Verge is a scrypt based alternative cryptocurrency trying to take the popularity of both Dogecoin and Bitcoin and combine it with the anonymous features of DASH. The block time is 30 seconds and the coin operates through Proof of Work. VERGE prides itself on being a symbol of progression in the cryptocurrency world. It is a more secure, private, and evolving cryptocurrency that is backed by bitcoin, a ton of developer resources and privacy tools.

name: Stratis
description: Stratis (STRAT) is a Proof-of-Stake (PoS) cryptocurrency with limited emission and low inflation. The Stratis blockchain known as the Statis Development Platform allows businesses and organizations to develop blockchain applications in C# utilizing the Microsoft .NET Framework. ???The Cloud Stratis platform allows developers to quickly provision full blockchain nodes to test their applications. The Cloud Stratis platform can also provision Blockchain nodes for Bitcoin, Ethereum and Bitshares, if the developer wants to develop an application specifically for one of these existing blockchains.

name: Version
description: Vertcoin, released on January 11th, 2014, is a cryptocurrency designed to resist the advent of both custom mining hardware and of multipool mining. Vertcoin employs a Scrypt-Adaptive-Nfactor hashing algorithm to provide resistance against application specific integrated circuits (ASICs).
